Step 1. Create The Hosted Zone With Same Name As Hostinger Domain Name

Launch The EC2 instance by using the instance-setup-script

Login AWS Console -> Search Bar -> Route 53 -> Get started -> Create hosted zones -> Get started -> Domain name -> Name(Same Name As Hostinger Domain Name) -> 
Create hosted zone -> Create record -> Quick create record -> Value(Copy And Paste The Public IP of The Instance) -> Create records -> 



Step 2. Add The NS Nameservers In Hostinger

Login Hostinger -> Domains -> Domain portfolio -> Click On Domain name -> DNS / Nameservers -> Change Nameservers -> Change nameservers -> Copy And Paste The NS Nameservers From Route 53 -> Save


Example:

ns-123.awsdns-45.com
ns-456.awsdns-67.net
ns-789.awsdns-32.org
ns-321.awsdns-12.co.uk
